SIMPLE: trifle
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trifle
<hw>Tri"fle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>trifle</ets>, <ets>trufle</ets>, OF. <ets>trufle</ets> mockery,
raillery, trifle, probably the same word as F. <ets>truffe</ets>
truffle, the word being applied to any small or worthless object. See
<er>Truffle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A thing of very little value
or importance; a paltry, or trivial, affair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With such poor <qex>trifles</qex> playing.</q>
<rj><qau>Drayton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Trifles</qex> light as air⟦br⟧
Are to the jealous confirmation strong⟦br⟧
As proofs of holy writ.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Small sands the mountain, moments make year,⟦br⟧
And <qex>frifles</qex> life.</q> <rj><qau>Young.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A dish composed of sweetmeats, fruits, cake, wine,
etc., with syllabub poured over it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trifle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Trifle
<hw>Tri"fle</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Trifled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Trifling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>trifelen</ets>, <ets>truflen</ets>. See <er>Trifle</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>To act or talk without seriousness, gravity,
weight, or dignity; to act or talk with levity; to indulge in light or
trivial amusements.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They <qex>trifle</qex>, and they beat the air about nothing which
toucheth us.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To trifle with</b></col>, <cd>to play the fool with; to
treat without respect or seriousness; to mock; as, <xex>to trifle
with</xex> one's feelings, or with sacred things.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trifle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Trifle
<hw>Tri"fle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make of no
importance; to treat as a trifle.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To spend in vanity; to fritter away; to waste;
<as>as, to <ex>trifle</ex> away money</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧We
<xex>trifle</xex> time.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trifler</ent>⟦br⟧
